The article is a statement by the President of the United States on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of the reunification of East and West Germany. The President highlights the historic achievement of the peaceful reunification and emphasizes the shared vision of a united Europe. The statement pays tribute to the contributions of Germany as a close ally and friend of the United States and acknowledges the courage and conviction of the German people in bringing down the Berlin Wall. The President expresses pride in the role played by the United States in defending a free Berlin and supporting Germany's quest for human dignity. The statement concludes by congratulating the people of Germany on their National Day and expressing gratitude for the vital friendship between the two nations.